thread.title: Redskins-Jets Winners & Losers

author: Jamie Mottram
title: Redskins-Jets Winners & Losers
text:
Handing out labels following Skins games, this time a 34-20 loss in New York. Winners 
Bashaud Breeland — Two fumble recoveries and one awesome interception in the first half alone. Chris says he’s getting a Breeland jersey. He should just modify his Portis; it’s best not to commit. 
Dustin Hopkins — I love this man and his touchbacks and 50-plus-yard field goals. Kirk Cousins has 4 multi-interception games in 6 weeks, the same number Robert Griffin III had in 37 games across his first three seasons. 
— Matt Ufford (@mattufford) October 19, 2015 Losers 
Kirk Cousins — Quarterbacks of mediocre teams with decent defenses and nominally run-focused offenses aren’t asked to do very much. Just “manage the game,” really, meaning don’t turn it over. But Cousins has four multi-interception games already this season, all Redskins losses. Today’s performance was so poor it won’t be much of a surprise if Jay Gruden, acting president of the Kirk Cousins Fan Club , turns to Colt McCoy next week. Pierre Garçon wipes Revis Island off the map: pic.twitter.com/tBcqHtq4lY 
— Burgundy Blog (@BurgundyBlog) October 18, 2015 Medium 
Pierre Garcon — Only 25 yards, but at least he shook Revis Island to its very core. Post navigation
